                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1153 St 2/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Blair</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase—Extracts]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-02-01T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 1, 1928—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Reference your 12, January 31, 3 p.m.<note n="13" xml:id="d711fn13">Not
                        printed.</note> Instructions are hereby given you to leave for Paris and
                    London to confer on the oil question and to remain absent from Madrid, where
                        Grummon<note n="14" xml:id="d711fn14">Stuart B. Grummon, third secretary of
                        Embassy.</note> will take charge, not more than a week. …</p>
                <p>Your French colleague may be confidentially informed of this mission. If the
                    American Embassy in Paris so desires, you may, at your discretion and in
                    conjunction with it, informally discuss the situation with the Foreign Office
                    there. In view of the British attitude, however, the Department entertains
                    doubts as to the wisdom of reporting the reason of your London visit either to
                    your British colleague or to the British Foreign Office. You may cable from
                    Paris or London for any further desired instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
